use
@Bean
@Scope can be this
ConfigurableBeanFactory.SCOPE_PROTOTYPE, ConfigurableBeanFactory.SCOPE_SINGLETON,
org.springframework.web.context.WebApplicationContext.SCOPE_REQUEST,
org.springframework.web.context.WebApplicationContext.SCOPE_SESSION,


singleton (default) only one object will created and shared
prototype :  where every making requet new project is given
request : when request to dispacther servlet then create object and request over destroy object
session : when any use login create bean when he logout destroy
